{
  "stem": "18281.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This is the famous blood libel that Jews-- the fact that we eat kosher and that the blood is being removed from animals before a Jew would eat it was misunderstood by the Christians.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they believed that, that, that, that blood that we remove from animals is being used in a religious ceremony and that we used the blood of children to do that.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There were-- cases like that primarily were in the countryside.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Somehow, I believe that in a big city, the police wouldn't believe such stories.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I'm not talking about the Middle Ages.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I'm talking about my lifetime.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But in the countryside to this day, there's a village in Austria that believes that, that is praying to a child that was murdered.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they all know the Jews did it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't remember.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But it's been documented quite often, that little village that still believe that this child was murdered by the Jews.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, I do not.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I've seen this in documentaries and that.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And this little village, I couldn't tell you the name of it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Right.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Right.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, it was, it was-- it was probably Sunday, the 15th of March, 1938.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Anschluss-- on, on the 13th of March, Austria was supposed to have an election for or against.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It's funny that they had a referendum, just like the one in, in Quebec.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the answer was yes or no for Austria to become to stay independent or join the Reich.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And this election or referendum was interrupted by the, the attack of the German army.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, first of all, we were-- we were stopped at the Austrian-Swiss border.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And even though we still had Austrian customs agents at the border, we were, we were really searched.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
